message.content: Based on the process list extracted from the memory image, the most likely process responsible for the initial exploit is "AcroRd32.exe" which is Adobe Acrobat Reader. This process was spawned by "firefox.exe" which indicates that the PDF file was opened using the Firefox browser. The exploit could have been triggered through a vulnerability in Adobe Acrobat Reader while opening the PDF file. Further analysis of the memory image should focus on these processes for any suspicious activities or indicators of compromise related to the exploit.
